    <section class="py-24 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8">
            <div class="text-center mb-16">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">Common Questions</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-slate-500 font-medium">Everything you need to know about the new era of search.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="group border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden hover:border-blue-300 transition-colors">
                    <div class="p-6 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-white group-hover:bg-blue-50/30">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800">How does Ranklore "read" AI responses?</h3>
                        <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold text-xl group-hover:rotate-90 transition-transform">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                        We use a proprietary network of API nodes to query LLMs (ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, etc.) at scale. We simulate thousands of natural language prompts to see exactly how your brand is being described and cited in real-time.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden hover:border-blue-300 transition-colors">
                    <div class="p-6 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-white group-hover:bg-blue-50/30">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800">Can you actually influence what an AI says?</h3>
                        <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold text-xl group-hover:rotate-90 transition-transform">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                        Yes. While you can't "pay for ads" inside a chat, you can optimize the data sources these models rely on. Ranklore identifies which of your pages are being indexed (or ignored) and provides a roadmap for content updates that AI models prioritize.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden hover:border-blue-300 transition-colors">
                    <div class="p-6 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-white group-hover:bg-blue-50/30">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800">Is this different from traditional SEO?</h3>
                        <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold text-xl group-hover:rotate-90 transition-transform">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                        Absolutely. Traditional SEO focuses on keywords and backlinks for a blue-link result. **Generative Engine Optimization (GEO)** focuses on context, attribution, and being the "cited source" within a generated paragraph.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden hover:border-blue-300 transition-colors">
                    <div class="p-6 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center bg-white group-hover:bg-blue-50/30">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800">How often is the data updated?</h3>
                        <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold text-xl group-hover:rotate-90 transition-transform">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                        Depending on your plan, we scan the AI landscape daily or weekly. Because models like Perplexity and Gemini have "live" web access, your brand's narrative can change in hours. We make sure you're the first to know.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="mt-12 text-center">
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Have more specific questions? <a href="#" class="text-blue-600 font-semibold underline decoration-blue-200 hover:decoration-blue-600">Chat with our team.</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
